[7] USA (Utah)
Date: Mon 18 Jul 2011
Source: Daily Reporter, Associated Press report [edited]
http://www.greenfieldreporter.com/view/story/48fd01744bf5443ba35aa196f2e9f0e9/UT--Measles-Outbreak/


Health officials say a reported case of measles in northern Utah has
turned out to be a false positive. The Bear River Health Department
announced on 11 Jul 2011 that it had 6 cases of measles in Cache
County [See part [7] of Measles update 2011 (23) 20110717.2169.]. The
agency now says that 6th case wasn't measles after all.

The Utah Department of Health says 9 cases of measles were confirmed
in Salt Lake County earlier this year [2011] and one in central Utah.
Bear River Health Department spokeswoman Jill Parker says the 1st case
in Cache County involved a child exposed in mid-May 2011. Officials
say those born after 1957 who haven't received 2 vaccine doses should
get immunized. These are the 1st Utah cases since 2005.

--
