Australasia
--------
[8] New Zealand (Auckland)
Date: Mon 18 Jul 2011
Source: Auckland stuff [abbreviated & edited]
http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/local-news/5302227/Measles-outbreak-increases-72-infected


Auckland's measles outbreak is up to 72 cases reported, and officials
say the disease is likely to spread. [Previously, the total was given
as 64 in part [10] of Measles update 2011 (23) 20110717.2169. -
Mod.CP]. Five people have been hospitalised so far from the disease,
which has mostly occurred in West Auckland, with some having spread to
Central Auckland, North Shore and Manukau.

Medical Officer of Health Dr Richard Hoskins urged parents to take
care during the school holidays to stop measles spreading. "If your
child is unwell or you suspect they have been exposed to measles and
are not up to date with MMR immunisations, we would ask that you
refrain from sending them to any scheduled group activities including
community gatherings."

Of the over 400 people contacted by the Auckland Regional Public
Health Service over the outbreak, not counting schools, "over 200 have
been assessed as immune to measles and do not need to be in
quarantine," he says. Five people are currently in quarantine.

The outbreak was 1st connected to an unimmunised child who attended
Oratia District School in West Auckland. Another was attributed to a
Thai Airways flight, TG491, which landed in Auckland on 19 Jun 2011
with a passenger suffering from the early stages of the infection.

--
